'''特朗普零容忍移民政策'''（Trump administration family separation policy）是美国第45任总统[[唐納·川普|唐納·川普]]執政時推出的針對非法移民的政策。2018年4月至2018年6月期間，特朗普政府在整个[[美墨邊界|美墨边境]]開始實施該政策。根据该政策，美國聯邦政府将偷渡到美國的非法移民與其子女強制分離<ref name="transcript">{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/transcript-sen-susan-collins-on-face-the-nation-june-17-2018/|title=Transcript: Sen. Susan Collins on 'Face the Nation'|date=June 17, 2018|work=[[面對國家|面對國家]]|accessdate=June 17, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191003070750/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/transcript-sen-susan-collins-on-face-the-nation-june-17-2018/|archivedate=October 3, 2019|publisher=[[CBS新聞|CBS新聞]]}}</ref><ref name="Everett">{{Cite news|url=https://www.politico.com/story/2018/06/17/children-separated-border-flake-collins-650779|title=GOP senators demand details from Trump administration about separated families|author=Everett|first=Burgess|date=June 17, 2018|work=[[政客_(媒体)|政客 (媒体)]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190210235907/https://www.politico.com/story/2018/06/17/children-separated-border-flake-collins-650779|archivedate=February 10, 2019|quote=...{{nbs}}'a number of media outlets have reported instances where parents and children seeking asylum at a port of entry have been separated,' the two senators wrote. 'These accounts and others like them concern us.' Flake and Collins cited a ''Washington Post'' story about a Honduran woman seeking asylum being separated from her child in Texas and a case in California in which a Congolese woman was separated from her daughter for months.}}</ref>。成年非法移民將被美國政府起诉并被关押在联邦监狱或被驱逐出境，而非法移民的子女则由[[美国卫生及公共服务部|美国卫生及公共服务部]]負責看護。后来有调查发现，零容忍移民政策在美國政府公开宣布實施的前一年就已经开始實施<ref name="auto9">{{Cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/2019/02/07/democrats-trump-administration-family-separation-policy-border-immigration/2794324002/|title=Democrats grill Trump administration officials over family separation policy on the border|author=Gomez|first=Alan|date=February 7, 2019|work=[[今日美國|今日美國]]|accessdate=March 11, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190222062921/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/2019/02/07/democrats-trump-administration-family-separation-policy-border-immigration/2794324002/|archivedate=February 22, 2019}}</ref>。

由於該政策受到不少非議，2018年6月20日，特朗普签署行政命令，決定终止該政策。2018年6月26日，[[美国联邦法官|美国联邦法官]]{{link-en|达娜·萨伯劳|Dana Sabraw}}在美國全国范围内发布了针对特朗普零容忍移民政策的禁令，并下令在30天内要让所有非法移民的子女与其父母团聚 <ref name="FedJudgeInjunction">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/06/26/us/politics/family-separations-congress-states.html|first2=Julie Hirschfeld|authorlink2=Julie Hirschfeld Davis|authorlink=Michael D. Shear|first4=Robert|last4=Pear|first3=Thomas|last3=Kaplan|author2=Davis|title=Federal Judge in California Halts Splitting of Migrant Families at Border|archivedate=June 27, 2018|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20180627133903/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/06/26/us/politics/family-separations-congress-states.html|work=[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]|date=June 26, 2018|first=Michael D.|author=Shear|authorlink4=Robert Pear}}</ref> <ref name="PrelimInjunctionText">[https://www.politico.com/f/?id=00000164-3f39-d1bc-afef-7fbbdf010001 |title=Order Granting Plaintiffs' Motion for Classwide Preliminary Injunction] {{Wayback|url=https://www.politico.com/f/?id=00000164-3f39-d1bc-afef-7fbbdf010001 |date=20200725133446 }}, ''Ms. L., et al. v. U.S. immigration & Customs Enforcement, et al.'', Case No. 18-cv-0428 (S.D. Cal. June 26, 2018).</ref>。两个月后，许多非法移民家庭仍处于分离状态。2020年1月，[[南方贫困法律中心|南方贫困法律中心]]表示，美國政府根据该政策，共有4368名兒童被迫與父母或監護人分離<ref>{{Cite web|title=Family separation under the Trump administration – a timeline|url=https://www.splcenter.org/news/2020/06/17/family-separation-under-trump-administration-timeline|accessdate=June 19, 2020|author=timeline|work=Southern Poverty Law Center|archive-date=2020-10-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201006152106/https://www.splcenter.org/news/2020/06/17/family-separation-under-trump-administration-timeline|dead-url=no}}</ref>。同样在1月，[[美國公民自由聯盟|美國公民自由聯盟]]表示，自2018年6月美國政府表示不再将非法移民與其子女強制分離以來，依然有超过1100个非法移民家庭未能團聚<ref name="npr">{{Cite web|title=Looking At Lasting Effects Of Trump's Family Separation Policy At The Southern Border|url=https://www.npr.org/2020/01/01/792916538/looking-at-lasting-effects-of-trumps-family-separation-policy-at-the-southern-bo|accessdate=October 16, 2020|author=transcript|work=NPR|archive-date=2020-10-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201013103605/https://www.npr.org/2020/01/01/792916538/looking-at-lasting-effects-of-trumps-family-separation-policy-at-the-southern-bo|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2020年11月，仍有666名非法移民子女的父母未能找到<ref name="The Washington Post">{{Cite news|title=The Trump administration's legacy of orphans|url=https://wapo.st/2PH2h2m?tid=ss_mail|accessdate=8 September 2018|work=The Washington Post|date=August 26, 2018|language=en|archive-date=2020-10-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201002061931/https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/the-trump-administrations-legacy-of-orphans/2018/08/26/820df666-a7e0-11e8-97ce-cc9042272f07_story.html?tid=ss_mail|dead-url=no}}</ref>。非法移民家庭团聚的過程得不到美國政府的任何財政支持，一些志愿者组织伸出援手幫助非法移民的子女與其父母團聚<ref>{{Cite web|title=Why hundreds of migrant children remain separated from their parents|url=https://www.pbs.org/newshour/show/why-hundreds-of-migrant-children-remain-separated-from-their-parents#transcript|accessdate=October 22, 2020|author=transcript|work=PBS News Hour|archive-date=2020-10-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201022121014/https://www.pbs.org/newshour/show/why-hundreds-of-migrant-children-remain-separated-from-their-parents#transcript|dead-url=no}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|title=Lawyers: We can't find parents of 545 kids separated by Trump administration|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/immigration/lawyers-say-they-can-t-find-parents-545-migrant-children-n1244066|accessdate=2020-10-21|work=NBC News|language=en|archive-date=2020-10-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201020232102/https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/immigration/lawyers-say-they-can-t-find-parents-545-migrant-children-n1244066|dead-url=no}}</ref> <ref name="Dickerson">{{Cite news|author=Dickerson|first=Caitlin|title=Parents of 545 Children Separated at the Border Cannot Be Found|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/10/21/us/migrant-children-separated.html|accessdate=22 October 2020|work=The New York Times|date=21 October 2020|archive-date=2020-10-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201021225526/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/10/21/us/migrant-children-separated.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2021年2月2日，美国第46任总统[[喬·拜登|喬·拜登]]頒布行政令，要求让因零容忍移民政策而在美墨边境被拆散的移民家庭重新团聚<ref>{{Cite web|title=拜登下令成立工作组，让在边境上被拆散的移民家庭重聚|url=https://cn.wsj.com/articles/%E6%8B%9C%E7%99%BB%E4%B8%8B%E4%BB%A4%E6%88%90%E7%AB%8B%E5%B7%A5%E4%BD%9C%E7%BB%84%EF%BC%8C%E8%AE%A9%E5%9C%A8%E8%BE%B9%E5%A2%83%E4%B8%8A%E8%A2%AB%E6%8B%86%E6%95%A3%E7%9A%84%E7%A7%BB%E6%B0%91%E5%AE%B6%E5%BA%AD%E9%87%8D%E8%81%9A-11612329910|accessdate=|author=華爾街日報|date=|format=|publisher=|language=|archive-date=2021-04-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210420221819/https://cn.wsj.com/articles/%E6%8B%9C%E7%99%BB%E4%B8%8B%E4%BB%A4%E6%88%90%E7%AB%8B%E5%B7%A5%E4%BD%9C%E7%BB%84%EF%BC%8C%E8%AE%A9%E5%9C%A8%E8%BE%B9%E5%A2%83%E4%B8%8A%E8%A2%AB%E6%8B%86%E6%95%A3%E7%9A%84%E7%A7%BB%E6%B0%91%E5%AE%B6%E5%BA%AD%E9%87%8D%E8%81%9A-11612329910|dead-url=no}}</ref>，並且拜登成立跨部门工作组，協助解决非法移民骨肉分离问题<ref>{{cite news |title=拜登宣布成立工作组解决非法移民“骨肉分离”问题 |url=https://www.chinanews.com/gj/2021/02-03/9403621.shtml |accessdate=2021-09-22 |archive-date=2021-02-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213232124/http://www.chinanews.com/gj/2021/02-03/9403621.shtml |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

